        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 9 at 12:40AM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 1239 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles northwest of Brice, or 12 miles southwest of Clarendon, moving
southwest at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of southern Donley
County.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
